<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="323" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">211.68/159</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 1887</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-30">September 30, 1937</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    October 19.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reference to the Department’s
                                telegram No. 36 of September 29, 1937, I have the honor to report
                                that I have today addressed a Note<note n="23" xml:id="d323fn23">Not
                                    printed.</note> to His Excellency John Metaxas, President of the
                                Council and Minister for Foreign Affairs, formally withdrawing the
                                notice of abrogation of the Extradition Treaty of May 6, 1931,
                                between the United States and Greece, which was delivered to the
                                Greek Government on November 6, 1933,<note n="24" xml:id="d323fn24">Note dated November 5, 1933, <ref target="frus1933v02#pg_565"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1933, vol.
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 565</ref>.</note>
                                pursuant to the Department’s telegraphic instruction No. 55 of
                                November 4, 1933.<note n="23" xml:id="d323fn25">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                            <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harold
                                Shantz</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>